If it weren't for him, 

551
00:41:29,550 --> 00:41:32,660
the family name would have died out. 

552
00:41:32,660 --> 00:41:36,860
Anggeum must treasure him. 

553
00:41:36,860 --> 00:41:39,280
You shouldn't treasure your children. 

554
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:41,490
You should love them, 

555
00:41:41,490 --> 00:41:43,860
but you must be strict with them. 

556
00:41:44,430 --> 00:41:45,990
You're right. 

557
00:41:45,990 --> 00:41:49,190
If you love your children, you must be strict. 

558
00:41:50,590 --> 00:41:52,840
You're upset about Subak, aren't you? 

559
00:41:56,410 --> 00:41:59,800
You must feel like you lost your right hand. 

560
00:42:00,820 --> 00:42:03,480
You could rely on Minjung before, 

561
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:05,940
but now, he lost it all. 

562
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:10,350
When your children are in trouble, it breaks your heart. 

563
00:42:13,450 --> 00:42:17,140
Oh, the trouble we're in right now... 

564
00:42:17,140 --> 00:42:19,730
The Korean War was nothing compared to this. 

565
00:42:20,540 --> 00:42:23,630
I wish I could help them out. 

566
00:42:23,630 --> 00:42:29,210
You raised them and married them off. 

567
00:42:29,210 --> 00:42:31,020
What else could you do? 

568
00:42:31,020 --> 00:42:32,900
If it weren't for him, 

569
00:42:32,900 --> 00:42:36,280
I would help them out with my severance pay and get them a better apartment. 

570
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:37,950
Don't be so stupid. 

571
00:42:38,590 --> 00:42:39,350
Excuse me? 

572
00:42:39,350 --> 00:42:41,940
Don't let them take advantage of you. 

573
00:42:41,940 --> 00:42:44,500
Don't let your kids suck you dry. 

574
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:47,890
Leave your severance pay alone. 

575
00:42:47,890 --> 00:42:51,700
You need money when you're old. 

576
00:42:51,700 --> 00:42:56,020
Don't give it to anyone.
Hold onto it. 

577
00:42:57,030 --> 00:42:59,170
And don't give it to Anggeum, understand? 

578
00:43:13,100 --> 00:43:14,090
Hello? 

579
00:43:14,090 --> 00:43:16,500
How can you sleep?
How can you? 

580
00:43:16,500 --> 00:43:18,360
Oh, mom. 

581
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:20,520
Don't you feel bad for your sister? 

582
00:43:21,100 --> 00:43:24,750
How can you sleep after seeing her like that? 

583
00:43:24,750 --> 00:43:26,290
You're heartless. 

584
00:43:26,290 --> 00:43:28,630
How could you be like that? 

585
00:43:28,630 --> 00:43:30,870
You're really something. 

586
00:43:30,870 --> 00:43:34,850
I feel lost after seeing her like that, and you're sleeping? 

587
00:43:34,850 --> 00:43:36,770
You're heartless. I'm hanging up. 

588
00:43:50,660 --> 00:43:51,810
Ugh... 

589
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:28,060
Oh, you're Sintong's aunt! 

590
00:44:28,060 --> 00:44:29,970
- Hello.
- Where are you going? 

591
00:44:29,970 --> 00:44:32,240
To my mom's house. 

592
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:37,700
You look pretty bad for someone who was in the Miss Korea pageant. 

593
00:44:37,700 --> 00:44:40,300
You look awful. 

594
00:44:40,300 --> 00:44:42,270
What happened to you? 

595
00:44:42,550 --> 00:44:44,990
Oh, I heard you have mice at your place. 

596
00:44:44,990 --> 00:44:46,550
Yes and roaches. 

597
00:44:46,550 --> 00:44:47,850
But I'm in a hurry. 

598
00:44:47,850 --> 00:44:51,710
I heard your husband is in parcel service. 

599
00:44:51,710 --> 00:44:53,990
My son works at a hotel. 

600
00:44:53,990 --> 00:44:56,420
I heard. Congratulations. Goodbye. 

601
00:44:56,420 --> 00:44:59,220
It must be really tough for you. 

602
00:44:59,220 --> 00:45:02,660
Why don't you get a job, like Hobak? 

603
00:45:02,660 --> 00:45:04,560
I'm in a hurry. 

604
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:06,030
I know. 

605
00:45:06,030 --> 00:45:08,520
Should I ask around? 

606
00:45:08,520 --> 00:45:10,140
You have a college degree, right? 

607
00:45:10,140 --> 00:45:12,900
I must get going. 

608
00:45:12,900 --> 00:45:15,630
Why are you sweating? 

609
00:45:15,630 --> 00:45:18,270
You look sick.
Would you like to sit down? 

610
00:45:18,270 --> 00:45:20,970
It's okay.
I'll see you again. 

611
00:45:46,660 --> 00:45:49,240
I'm not going to let her get away with it. 

612
00:45:49,750 --> 00:45:51,220
What's wrong with her? 

613
00:45:51,220 --> 00:45:53,000
Why couldn't she just let her go? 

614
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:58,380
I can't believe I'm washing poo out of my daughter's pants. 

615
00:45:58,380 --> 00:46:00,670
- What are you doing?
- Mother! 

616
00:46:00,670 --> 00:46:03,460
What are you washing? 

617
00:46:03,460 --> 00:46:05,320
It doesn't concern you. 

618
00:46:07,220 --> 00:46:09,420
Is someone making fermented soybeans? 

619
00:46:10,290 --> 00:46:11,850
Fermented soybeans? 

620
00:46:11,850 --> 00:46:15,050
Who's making that? Who? 

621
00:46:15,050 --> 00:46:16,910
It smells really good. 

622
00:46:16,910 --> 00:46:20,390
Hey, let's make some too. 

623
00:46:20,390 --> 00:46:25,800
I've been craving fermented soybeans for a couple days now. 

624
00:46:25,800 --> 00:46:28,780
Please don't mention that. 

625
00:46:48,520 --> 00:46:49,410
Yes, Daese. 

626
00:46:49,410 --> 00:46:54,540
Sunjeong, I'm getting a package today. 

627
00:46:54,540 --> 00:46:56,160
Okay. 

628
00:47:33,200 --> 00:47:34,300
Hello. 

629
00:47:34,300 --> 00:47:36,760
What's up, little girl? 

630
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:40,930
I'm not a little girl.
I'm Daebak's girlfriend. 

631
00:47:40,930 --> 00:47:42,430
I know. 

632
00:47:42,430 --> 00:47:45,200
You're the little girl who's after Daebak. 

633
00:47:46,750 --> 00:47:49,110
I'm not after him. 

634
00:47:49,110 --> 00:47:50,860
What do you want? 

635
00:47:50,860 --> 00:47:53,950
Daebak's at the teachers office. 

636
00:47:53,950 --> 00:47:56,980
I need to talk to you. 

637
00:48:00,330 --> 00:48:03,470
Me? About what? 

638
00:48:09,460 --> 00:48:11,880
What's this? 

639
00:48:11,880 --> 00:48:13,720
It's a yellow card. 

640
00:48:13,720 --> 00:48:15,180
A yellow card? 

641
00:48:15,180 --> 00:48:18,340
They use this when they play soccer. 

642
00:48:18,340 --> 00:48:20,330
You know what it means, don't you? 

643
00:48:20,330 --> 00:48:22,130
Don't flirt with Daebak again. 

644
00:48:22,130 --> 00:48:25,720
If you do, I'm giving you a red card. 

645
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:28,350
You know what comes after that, don't you? 

646
00:48:28,350 --> 00:48:29,350
Expulsion. 

647
00:48:31,270 --> 00:48:32,350
What are you doing? 

648
00:48:33,850 --> 00:48:35,880
What are you doing at my school? 

649
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:37,460
Daebak, I was waiting for you. 

650
00:48:37,460 --> 00:48:39,190
Let's go, Daebak. 

651
00:48:39,190 --> 00:48:40,720
Hold on. 

652
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:41,970
Are you going to the academy? 

653
00:48:43,030 --> 00:48:44,180
Daebak! 

654
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:47,750
Fine, I'm coming. 

655
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:52,530
Daebak, what should we eat? 

656
00:48:53,690 --> 00:48:55,580
Oh, she's cute. 

657
00:48:55,580 --> 00:48:57,090
She's so funny. 

658
00:48:57,090 --> 00:48:59,810
Daebak is incredible. 

659
00:49:12,870 --> 00:49:14,540
Bye, Haebak! 

660
00:49:34,620 --> 00:49:35,750
Hello. 

661
00:49:43,730 --> 00:49:45,720
I want to send this by certified mail. 

662
00:49:45,720 --> 00:49:46,470
Okay. 

663
00:49:55,790 --> 00:49:59,900
He asked me for my high school yearbooks. 

664
00:49:59,900 --> 00:50:03,400
So I told him they got lost in the fire. 

665
00:50:04,380 --> 00:50:07,710
Slap them on the mouth when they say that. 

666
00:50:07,710 --> 00:50:08,610
How dare they... 

667
00:50:08,610 --> 00:50:09,800
Hey, hey! 

668
00:50:09,800 --> 00:50:11,690
If that's who you'd set me up with, forget it! 

669
00:50:12,740 --> 00:50:14,190
How dare she! 

670
00:50:15,380 --> 00:50:17,330
You can't tell I got work done. 

671
00:50:17,330 --> 00:50:19,640
Everyone gets that much work done. 

672
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:21,480
You can't tell you got any. 

673
00:50:21,480 --> 00:50:22,890
Don't you agree? 

674
00:50:24,140 --> 00:50:25,050
Excuse me? 

675
00:50:25,050 --> 00:50:27,710
You're too young to have worries! 

676
00:50:27,710 --> 00:50:29,500
Your face is filled with worries. 

677
00:50:29,500 --> 00:50:31,920
I can tell you have some sad stories to tell. 

678
00:50:32,880 --> 00:50:33,720
Oh. 

679
00:50:33,720 --> 00:50:36,600
There are rumors about you. 

680
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:39,080
Rumors? 

681
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:44,150
They're saying you living with your brother in law is weird. 

682
00:50:44,470 --> 00:50:46,630
Is it okay to live with your brother in law? 

683
00:50:46,630 --> 00:50:48,380
I guess you could. 

684
00:50:48,380 --> 00:50:51,730
If they're divorced, it should be fine. 

685
00:50:52,270 --> 00:50:53,730
It's not like that. 

686
00:50:53,730 --> 00:50:55,640
I have a reason. 

687
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:58,800
We are still related. 

688
00:51:00,340 --> 00:51:01,390
Aunt Sunjeong. 

689
00:51:02,320 --> 00:51:03,620
Yes? 

690
00:51:03,620 --> 00:51:04,550
Should I wait for you? 

691
00:51:04,550 --> 00:51:06,610
It's okay. You go ahead. I'll catch up. 

692
00:51:06,610 --> 00:51:08,510
Okay. Take your time and get more pretty. 

693
00:51:14,930 --> 00:51:17,380
Who's that? The son? 

694
00:51:17,380 --> 00:51:19,300
Yes, he's my nephew. 

695
00:51:21,500 --> 00:51:23,230
Oh, wow. 

696
00:51:27,690 --> 00:51:29,310
This car is... 

697
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:34,910
It's a wise choice. This car is... 

698
00:51:34,910 --> 00:51:35,930
Shh... 

699
00:51:43,950 --> 00:51:49,380
Yay! This is nutty, nutty, nuts! 

700
00:52:02,440 --> 00:52:03,910
This is nuts! 

701
00:52:03,910 --> 00:52:05,570
Hey! You stop right there! 

702
00:52:05,570 --> 00:52:07,970
Hey! Come here! 

703
00:52:07,970 --> 00:52:10,260
You! Hey! 

704
00:52:10,260 --> 00:52:11,390
Hey! 

705
00:52:13,010 --> 00:52:14,850
Are you out of your mind? Are you? 

706
00:52:14,850 --> 00:52:16,960
A car is a man's pride. 

707
00:52:16,960 --> 00:52:18,420
How dare you! 

708
00:52:20,550 --> 00:52:23,190
I'm going to kill you! 

709
00:52:24,880 --> 00:52:27,240
Hey, my shoes... 

710
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:35,560
So? I can't return it? 

711
00:52:36,380 --> 00:52:39,470
Hey! Who says I can't return a car? 

712
00:52:39,470 --> 00:52:40,790
Stop talking nonsense! 

713
00:52:40,790 --> 00:52:43,670
Hobak, open the door. 

714
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:45,920
Hobak. 

715
00:52:46,980 --> 00:52:48,900
Hobak, the door! 

716
00:52:49,880 --> 00:52:52,120
Hobak! Hobak! 

717
00:52:52,120 --> 00:52:53,680
You've been out here all this time? 

718
00:52:53,680 --> 00:52:55,950
Why are you back so late? 

719
00:52:55,950 --> 00:52:58,810
Hey! Open the door! My mom's here. 

720
00:52:58,810 --> 00:52:59,860
And the sister. 

721
00:52:59,860 --> 00:53:02,480
My sister's here, too.
Open the door! 

722
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:04,560
Hobak! 

723
00:53:05,660 --> 00:53:06,870
Open it! 

724
00:53:06,870 --> 00:53:08,190
No! 

725
00:53:08,190 --> 00:53:10,790
I need to teach him a lesson. 

726
00:53:10,790 --> 00:53:12,320
You're being really stuffy. 

727
00:53:12,320 --> 00:53:14,030
Everyone needs a car these days. 

728
00:53:14,030 --> 00:53:15,500
We should have one too. 

729
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:16,770
Of course! 

730
00:53:16,770 --> 00:53:20,280
Open! Open! Open! 

731
00:53:20,280 --> 00:53:21,680
What are you doing? 

732
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:27,260
Open! Open! Open! 

733
00:53:28,230 --> 00:53:31,150
Who doesn't have a car these days? 

734
00:53:31,150 --> 00:53:32,950
Mom, go for it. Open! 

735
00:53:32,950 --> 00:53:35,840
Open it now! You're embarrassing us. 

736
00:53:35,840 --> 00:53:39,330
- Open!
- He has a job. He can get a car! 

737
00:53:40,340 --> 00:53:41,850
Mother! 

738
00:53:47,740 --> 00:53:50,390
There's so many packages to deliver. 

739
00:53:50,980 --> 00:53:53,730
I don't think I can go home this year. 

740
00:53:53,730 --> 00:53:56,690
That's that, but why can't Subak come? 

741
00:53:56,690 --> 00:53:58,350
I can't send her alone. 

742
00:53:58,350 --> 00:53:59,650
Why not? 

743
00:53:59,650 --> 00:54:02,680
She's acting like that because of you! 

744
00:54:02,680 --> 00:54:05,570
She's been sick lately.
She hasn't been well. 

745
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:08,490
I'm sorry, Minsuk. 

746
00:54:09,750 --> 00:54:13,400
I'll drop by and see father another time. 

747
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:15,070
So please take care of... 

748
00:54:17,050 --> 00:54:18,110
Minsuk! 

749
00:54:19,390 --> 00:54:20,600
Hello? 

750
00:54:21,380 --> 00:54:22,600
Here. 

751
00:54:39,870 --> 00:54:41,620
What is it? 

752
00:54:41,620 --> 00:54:42,870
A chamber pot. 

753
00:54:49,580 --> 00:54:50,920
Use this. 

754
00:54:51,720 --> 00:54:54,220
Using the communal bathroom is hard,  

755
00:54:54,220 --> 00:54:56,820
and you can't run to your mother's place every time. 

756
00:54:56,820 --> 00:54:58,290
I don't want this. 

757
00:54:58,290 --> 00:54:59,570
I heard it's convenient. Use it. 

758
00:54:59,570 --> 00:55:00,930
I said no! 

759
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:04,700
Must you make me feel pathetic? 

760
00:55:05,030 --> 00:55:05,970
What do you mean? 

761
00:55:05,970 --> 00:55:08,020
You're making me feel pathetic. 

762
00:55:08,020 --> 00:55:11,070
Did you think I'd thank you for this? 

763
00:55:11,070 --> 00:55:12,760
It's embarrassing, humiliating, 

764
00:55:12,760 --> 00:55:15,130
and it feels like my face is on fire. 

765
00:55:15,130 --> 00:55:19,130
Do you know how embarrassing it is to not be able to hold it in? 

766
00:55:19,130 --> 00:55:21,430
And now you want me to use a chamber pot? 

767
00:55:21,430 --> 00:55:25,390
You know how I get constipated whenever I'm away from home! 

768
00:55:27,030 --> 00:55:28,410
We'll get through it. 

769
00:55:29,320 --> 00:55:30,770
It's only for 3 years. 

770
00:55:30,770 --> 00:55:33,510
How can I not poo for 3 years? 

771
00:55:33,510 --> 00:55:35,350
I'm not tell you to do that! 

772
00:55:35,350 --> 00:55:36,990
Use this. 

773
00:55:36,990 --> 00:55:38,400
Everyone else does it. 

774
00:55:38,400 --> 00:55:41,770
I got this at the market, and it means others use it too. 

775
00:55:41,770 --> 00:55:43,850
That's not embarrassing! Just go here! 

776
00:55:43,850 --> 00:55:46,030
Stop it! 

777
00:55:46,030 --> 00:55:48,990
I was in the Miss Korea pageant! 

778
00:55:53,060 --> 00:55:54,510
Oh, man! 

779
00:55:57,900 --> 00:55:58,850
A blind date? 

780
00:55:58,850 --> 00:55:59,830
Yes. 

781
00:55:59,830 --> 00:56:02,080
You saw her at the beauty salon. 

782
00:56:02,080 --> 00:56:04,320
I didn't. Is she pretty? 

783
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:06,760
I would've remembered if she were pretty. 

784
00:56:06,760 --> 00:56:08,760
She's got a face most men would like. 

785
00:56:08,760 --> 00:56:10,640
Would you like to meet her? 

786
00:56:10,640 --> 00:56:12,280
Why not? You're hooking us up after all. 

787
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:15,030
Not really. She asked me to. 

788
00:56:15,030 --> 00:56:16,930
She fell for you the moment she saw you. 

789
00:56:16,930 --> 00:56:19,220
So just give her a chance. 

790
00:56:19,220 --> 00:56:20,880
Okay. 

791
00:56:21,410 --> 00:56:22,880
Sangnam, 

792
00:56:23,700 --> 00:56:25,380
I'm saying this out of concern, 

793
00:56:25,380 --> 00:56:28,740
and I know I might be overreacting... 

794
00:56:28,740 --> 00:56:30,620
Don't beat around the bush. 

795
00:56:31,050 --> 00:56:33,380
Don't hold onto the past. 

796
00:56:33,380 --> 00:56:34,790
It'll only make your life hard. 

797
00:56:35,830 --> 00:56:38,180
Do you still have feelings for her? 

798
00:56:40,740 --> 00:56:44,800
She was your first, so it would be hard. 

799
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:48,400
But she broke your heart, so forget her. 

800
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:53,670
Sangnam, 

801
00:56:53,670 --> 00:56:58,450
I just want you to be happy. 

802
00:56:58,450 --> 00:57:01,250
Not pretending to be happy, 

803
00:57:02,190 --> 00:57:05,280
but really, truly happy. 

804
00:57:05,280 --> 00:57:06,890
You know what I mean, don't you? 

805
00:57:10,320 --> 00:57:12,260
I will be. 

806
00:57:12,260 --> 00:57:16,330
But I'd like to ask the same of you. 

807
00:57:16,330 --> 00:57:18,620
I want you to be happy, too. 

808
00:57:18,620 --> 00:57:22,010
I'm happy. I have everything I need. 

809
00:57:22,010 --> 00:57:23,570
Sangnam, let's go. 

810
00:57:23,570 --> 00:57:25,080
I'm coming. 

811
00:57:25,080 --> 00:57:27,850
Oh, aunt, your hair looks pretty. 

812
00:57:27,850 --> 00:57:29,750
You're the best. 

813
00:57:39,630 --> 00:57:41,120
I'm going to hell. 

814
00:57:52,520 --> 00:57:55,890
Bastard. I hope you're happy! 

815
00:57:55,890 --> 00:57:59,500
You don't trust anyone, do you? 

816
00:58:11,460 --> 00:58:13,920
I can't seem to be able to become like you. 

817
00:58:14,820 --> 00:58:16,930
It doesn't happen overnight. 

818
00:58:16,930 --> 00:58:18,600
Are you coming from somewhere? 

819
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:21,540
The academy. I got bored. 

820
00:58:21,540 --> 00:58:22,920
I thought your grades were bad. 

821
00:58:22,920 --> 00:58:25,950
The kid who's head of the class cries when he gets his report card. 

822
00:58:25,950 --> 00:58:27,480
I don't get it. 

823
00:58:27,480 --> 00:58:29,480
How much more must you study to not cry? 

824
00:58:31,570 --> 00:58:37,000
It seems like you're the only one who can be successful in your family so work hard. 

825
00:58:37,000 --> 00:58:39,610
